<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="915" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d915">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9748:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-09T18:00:00-05:00">April 9, 1941—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>39. Your 91, April 8, 5 p.m.<note n="50" xml:id="d915fn50">Not
                                    printed.</note> Reports recently made public here state that the
                                Yugoslav Minister in Ankara<note n="50a" xml:id="d915fn50a">Iliya
                                    Shumenkovich.</note> has informed the <pb facs="0852" n="844" xml:id="pg_844"/> Turkish Government that Bulgarian troops have
                                joined in the attack on Yugoslavia, implying that Turkey is being
                                called on to implement the Balkan Entente. Please comment.</p>
                            <p>The Department would appreciate being kept informed as fully and
                                continuously as possible regarding Turkey’s position vis-à-vis
                                present developments in the Balkans.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>